The paper deals with the problem of imbalanced learning in data streams, which is a common issue in machine learning. The proposed solution involves using the Hellinger distance measure as a decision tree split criterion, which is a technique commonly used in machine learning and data science. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.CV (Computer Vision), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
